# Appify Overview

An appify app replaces TiddlyWiki's default page layout with a grid-based app layout. Each app is a tiddler tagged `$:/tags/rimir/appify/app`.

## Core concepts

- **Layout**: A grid template (e.g., sidebar-main, topbar-sidebar-main) that defines named **slots**
- **Slots**: Grid areas where **view tiddlers** are rendered
- **View tiddlers**: Regular wikitext tiddlers assigned to slots via `appify-view-<slot>` fields on the app tiddler
- **Channels**: Named state variables (stored as `$:/state/rimir/statewrap/<appTitle>/<channel>` tiddlers). Views read channels with `[statewrap-get[channel]]` and set them with `<$action-statewrap-set channel="name" value="val"/>`
- **Rules**: Reactive logic in the app tiddler's body text — when one channel changes, other channels are automatically set

## App tiddler fields

- `appify-layout`: layout name (e.g., `topbar-sidebar-main`)
- `appify-channels`: space-separated channel names
- `appify-default-<channel>`: default value for a channel
- `appify-view-<slot>`: title of view tiddler for that slot
- `caption`: display name

## Samples vs user apps

The plugin ships sample apps as read-only blueprints under `$:/plugins/rimir/appify/samples/`. These must be cloned before use. Cloned apps live at `$:/config/rimir/appify/apps/<name>` and their views at `$:/config/rimir/appify/views/<name>`. Only cloned apps can be modified.

## What you can modify (on cloned apps)

- **Channel values**: set_field on the state tiddler to change app navigation/selection state
- **View tiddler wikitext**: set_field(field="text") to change what renders in a slot
- **App tiddler fields**: add channels, change defaults, change view bindings
- **App tiddler body**: modify reactive rules

